  "detailed_description": "<p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >This roguelite deckbuilder is set in the American West. Battle monsters, cultists, and folkloric creatures while searching for gold and the source of the evil within a mine. You choose when to leave, not where to go. Will you play it safe returning to the surface, or risk it all by going deeper?</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > </p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Battle</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2990670/extras/8f3810374aacf1c7c6f3b658e78c42f4.poster.avif?t=1757353152\" width=800 height=450 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2990670/extras/8f3810374aacf1c7c6f3b658e78c42f4.webm?t=1757353152\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2990670/extras/8f3810374aacf1c7c6f3b658e78c42f4.mp4?t=1757353152\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Turn-based combat gives you plenty of time to think strategically. Sometimes it’s best to retain cards by “pocketing” them for use in combos or when you most need them.</p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Make Choices</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2990670/extras/9b2c091591b6e4ce600dc65d4297c6ec.poster.avif?t=1757353152\" width=800 height=450 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2990670/extras/9b2c091591b6e4ce600dc65d4297c6ec.webm?t=1757353152\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2990670/extras/9b2c091591b6e4ce600dc65d4297c6ec.mp4?t=1757353152\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span>Many difficult decisions await you in the mine, including when to end your run and return to the surface with your loot. The deeper you go the better the rewards, but if you die you risk losing it all.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Purchase Upgrades</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2990670/extras/b9b4de937cd4dfd5aadc96e85f5ae4a5.poster.avif?t=1757353152\" width=800 height=450 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2990670/extras/b9b4de937cd4dfd5aadc96e85f5ae4a5.webm?t=1757353152\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2990670/extras/b9b4de937cd4dfd5aadc96e85f5ae4a5.mp4?t=1757353152\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span>Use the gold you acquire to expand your town, unlocking upgrades, new characters, and the ability to purchase cards and equipment for each character.</p>",
  "about_the_game": "<p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >This roguelite deckbuilder is set in the American West. Battle monsters, cultists, and folkloric creatures while searching for gold and the source of the evil within a mine. You choose when to leave, not where to go. Will you play it safe returning to the surface, or risk it all by going deeper?</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > </p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Battle</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2990670/extras/8f3810374aacf1c7c6f3b658e78c42f4.poster.avif?t=1757353152\" width=800 height=450 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2990670/extras/8f3810374aacf1c7c6f3b658e78c42f4.webm?t=1757353152\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2990670/extras/8f3810374aacf1c7c6f3b658e78c42f4.mp4?t=1757353152\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Turn-based combat gives you plenty of time to think strategically. Sometimes it’s best to retain cards by “pocketing” them for use in combos or when you most need them.</p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Make Choices</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2990670/extras/9b2c091591b6e4ce600dc65d4297c6ec.poster.avif?t=1757353152\" width=800 height=450 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2990670/extras/9b2c091591b6e4ce600dc65d4297c6ec.webm?t=1757353152\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2990670/extras/9b2c091591b6e4ce600dc65d4297c6ec.mp4?t=1757353152\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span>Many difficult decisions await you in the mine, including when to end your run and return to the surface with your loot. The deeper you go the better the rewards, but if you die you risk losing it all.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Purchase Upgrades</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2990670/extras/b9b4de937cd4dfd5aadc96e85f5ae4a5.poster.avif?t=1757353152\" width=800 height=450 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2990670/extras/b9b4de937cd4dfd5aadc96e85f5ae4a5.webm?t=1757353152\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2990670/extras/b9b4de937cd4dfd5aadc96e85f5ae4a5.mp4?t=1757353152\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span>Use the gold you acquire to expand your town, unlocking upgrades, new characters, and the ability to purchase cards and equipment for each character.</p>",
